request.description:
get all friends of a certain group.
call is:
/ServUpApi/v1/Contact/GetRelationsByGroup/{group}
call it like:
/ServUpApi/v1/Contact/GetRelationsByGroup/family

above call will return all friends belonging to the "family" group.

Removes the relation from your accepted contacts.
Accepts a list of public IDs

GetReceivedRelationsRequests
Incoming friend requests for you.
it gives u the list of all people who are adding you as a friend.

You can expect a reply like following:

[
  {
    "publicId": "57ea4ed77bbba435bce1c160",
    "mobileNumber": "333344444",
    "coverPictureURL": "http://sample.com/1.jpg",
    "relation": "Friend",
    "group": "Friend"
  }
]

CheckFriendRequestConfirmation

you can check the statuses of all requests that YOU have sent. that is, if the status is still pending, or have they accepted it.

expect a reply like:

[
  {
    "publicId": "57e8f94b7bbba4017089e756",
    "mobileNumber": "001111118423238",
    "coverPictureURL": "http://sample.com/1.jpg",
    "relation": "Friend",
    "group": "Friend"
  }
]

this is just duplication of the "User 1 adds User 2 as friend" already listed above it. 

uset this to add friends/family etc
